Mari asks Dawn about fashion: Variant A sets this marker to 1, and just has Mari ask for tips. Variants B and C set this marker to 2 and 3, respectively, and have Mari actually ask Dawn out on a shopping date.

Marks Mari's lines towards Dawn's Must Masturbate phase. The tens place of the value indicates the stage variant (A = 1, B = 2, C = 3), and the ones place indicates the particular line variant (1 or 2).

Mari asks Dawn about the relationship between her and the player: whether they're just friends, or something more.

Mari asks Dawn about how she and the player know each other. There are two variants here: the first variant (which sets this marker to 1) plays if the player has not played against Mari previously, and the second (which sets this marker to 2) plays if the player has done at least previous game with Mari.

Mari tells Dawn not to worry about her boyfriend-- she and Hero have an open relationship, so they're both fine with things like Mari going on a date with Dawn. She even suggests that Hero could join in, too. This plays once, immediately after any line where she asks Dawn out on a date.

Mari asks Dawn if she can tell any interesting stories about the player, since they seem to know each other.

Mari asks Dawn why she chose strip poker as a way to hang out with people. Variants B and C set this marker to 2 and 3, respectively, and have Mari ask if she's particularly interested in anyone at the table.
